User can also filter the visual with item kind slicer and add or remove columns using optional columns slicer.\n\n\n\nColumn definitions:\n\n\n\nDefault fields:\n\nIn this section lists the default fields that are displayed in the matrix by item and operation visual. You can''t remove default fields from the table.\n\nWorkspace - The workspace the item belongs to.\nItem kind - The item type.\nItem name - The item name.\nCU (s) - Capacity Units in seconds.\nDuration (s) - Processing time in seconds.\nUsers - The number of fabric users that used the item.\nBilling type - Displays information if the Item is billable or not.\n\n\nOptional fields:\n\nIn this section lists the optional fields that you can add to the matrix by item and operation visual. You can add or remove optional fields from the table using the Select optional column(s) dropdown menu.\n\nRejected count - The total number of rejected operations for an item.\nFailed count - The total number of failed operations for an item.\nInvalid count - The total number of invalid operations for an item.\nInProgress count - The total number of operations that are in progress for an item.\nSuccessful count - The total number of successful operations for an item.\nVirtualized item -Displays one of the following values:\nTrue - Virtual items that consume CUs, for example virtual items used by Copilot\n\nFalse - Items that aren''t virtual\n\nVirtualized workspace - Displays one of the following values:\nTrue - Virtual workspaces that consume CUs, for example a virtual workspace used by a virtual network\n\nFalse - Workspaces that aren''t virtual\n\nItem size (GB) - The amount of memory a item needs.\nOverloaded minutes - Displays a sum of 30 minutes increments were overloading occurred at least once.\nPerformance delta - Displays the performance effect on items. A positive value indicates that the performance is improving, and a negative value indicates that the performance is degrading. The color in the table represents the performance delta:              \n\t\t\t\t\tNo color - A value higher than -10\n\n\t\t\t\t\tOrange - A value between -10 and -25\n\n\t\t\t\t\tRed - A value lower than -25'"}}},"titleFontColor":{"solid":{"color":{"expr":{"Literal":{"Value":"'#1B1B1B'"}}}}},"background":{"solid":{"color":{"expr":{"Literal":{"Value":"'#FFFFFF'"}}}}},"transparency":{"expr":{"Literal":{"Value":"5D"}}}}}],"stylePreset":[{"properties":{"name":{"expr":{"Literal":{"Value":"'None'"}}}}}]}},"parentGroupName":"17b0c30081d4b33e8809"}

This chart displays the following elements:



Interactive %- Red columns represent the percentage consumption of CU(s) used during interactive operations in a 30 second period. Interactive operations cover a wide range of resources triggered by fabric users. These operations are associated with interactive page loads and are handled by backend cores.
Background % - Blue columns represent the percentage consumption of CU(s) used during background operations in a 30 second period. Background operations cover backend processes that are not directly triggered by fabric users, such as data refreshes. These operations are handled by backend cores.
Interactive Non-billable %- Green columns represent the percentage consumption of CU(s) used during interactive operations in a 30 second period for preview workload. 
Background Non-billable % - Sky Blue columns represent the percentage consumption of CU(s) used during background operations in a 30 second period for preview workloads. 
CU Limit - A solid grey line that shows Capacity Unit consumption without autoscale which is basically a constant line to show 100% CU(s) consumption.
Autoscale CU Limit - A yellow dotted line that shows the threshold of the allowed number of CU(s) for the selected capacity. Columns that stretch above this line, represent timepoints where the capacity is overloaded.

Interactive operations cover a wide range of resources triggered by fabric users. These operations are associated with interactive page loads and are handled by backend cores.
Background % - Blue columns represent the percentage consumption of CU(s) used during background operations in a 30 second period. Background operations cover backend processes that are not directly triggered by fabric users, such as data refreshes. These operations are handled by backend cores.
Interactive Non-billable %- Green columns represent the percentage consumption of CU(s) used during interactive operations in a 30 second period for preview workload. 
Background Non-billable % - Sky Blue columns represent the percentage consumption of CU(s) used during background operations in a 30 second period for preview workloads. 
CU Limit - A solid grey line that shows Capacity Unit consumption without autoscale which is basically a constant line to show 100% CU(s) consumption.
Autoscale CU Limit - A yellow dotted line that shows the threshold of the allowed number of CU(s) for the selected capacity. Columns that stretch above this line, represent timepoints where the capacity is overloaded.
